<div class="postright">
<h3>Re: Persistence mode</h3>
<div class="postmsg">
<p>This is the procedure I followed to make my microSD persistence Parrot and somehow worked.&#160; Hope it could help ur case.&#160; FYI</p><p>1. burn Parrot ISO to a USB u wish to use<br/>2. Boot from the new USB<br/>3. At the menu, select either persistence or encrypted persistence based on ur goal<br/>4. Once inside create a new partition using &#039;gparted&#039; for persistence<br/>5. Also referred to https://goo.gl/kGg89p as part of reference</p><p>Before this I tried making the persistence partition on the USB after I burned the ISO to microSD and before first booting into Parrot, but that took me nowhere for quite sometime.&#160; Hope this would somehow help u out.&#160; Have a nice weekend.</p><p>JC</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
