<div class="postright">
<h3>Re: Persistence mode</h3>
<div class="postmsg">
<p>Check the label of the new partition, it should be called &quot;persistence&quot;</p><p>Boot Live, or from other linux, and mount the partition as root, then write the conf file. Below is an example (im assuming that your persistence partition is sdb3, but you need to check it by yourself with fdisk -l)</p><p>mkdir -p /mnt/my_usb<br/>mount /dev/sdb3 /mnt/my_usb<br/>echo &quot;/ union&quot; &gt; /mnt/my_usb/persistence.conf<br/>umount /dev/sdb3</p>
</div>
